   123	_USCODE_42_6930_TEXT = (
   124	    "§6930. Effective date (a) Preliminary notification Not later than ninety days after "
   125	    "promulgation of regulations under section 6921 of this title identifying by its "
   126	    "characteristics or listing any substance as hazardous waste subject to this subchapter, any "
   127	    "person generating or transporting such substance or owning or operating a facility for "
   128	    "treatment, storage, or disposal of such substance shall file with the Administrator (or with "
   129	    "States having authorized hazardous waste permit programs under section 6926 of this title) a "
   130	    "notification stating the location and general description of such activity and the "
   131	    "identified or listed hazardous wastes handled by such person. Not later than fifteen months "
   132	    "after November 8, 1984— (1) the owner or operator of any facility which produces a fuel (A) "
   133	    "from any hazardous waste identified or listed under section 6921 of this title, (B) from "
   134	    "such hazardous waste identified or listed under section 6921 of this title and any other "
   135	    "material, (C) from used oil, or (D) from used oil and any other material; (2) the owner or "
   136	    "operator of any facility (other than a single- or two-family residence) which burns for "
   137	    "purposes of energy recovery any fuel produced as provided in paragraph (1) or any fuel which "
   138	    "otherwise contains used oil or any hazardous waste identified or listed under section 6921 "
   139	    "of this title; and (3) any person who distributes or markets any fuel which is produced as "
   140	    "provided in paragraph (1) or any fuel which otherwise contains used oil or any hazardous "
   141	    "waste identified or listed under section 6921 of this title 1 shall file with the "
   142	    "Administrator (and with the State in the case of a State with an authorized hazardous waste "
   143	    "program) a notification stating the location and general description of the facility, "
   144	    "together with a description of the identified or listed hazardous waste involved and, in the "
   145	    "case of a facility referred to in paragraph (1) or (2), a description of the production or "
   146	    "energy recovery activity carried out at the facility and such other information as the "
   147	    "Administrator deems necessary. For purposes of the preceding provisions, the term \"hazardous "
   148	    "waste listed under section 6921 of this title\" also includes any commercial chemical product "
   149	    "which is listed under section 6921 of this title and which, in lieu of its original intended "
   150	    "use, is (i) produced for use as (or as a component of) a fuel, (ii) distributed for use as a "
   151	    "fuel, or (iii) burned as a fuel. Notification shall not be required under the second "
   152	    "sentence of this subsection in the case of facilities (such as residential boilers) where "
   153	    "the Administrator determines that such notification is not necessary in order for the "
   154	    "Administrator to obtain sufficient information respecting current practices of facilities "
   155	    "using hazardous waste for energy recovery. Nothing in this subsection shall be construed to "
   156	    "affect or impair the provisions of section 6921(b)(3) of this title. Nothing in this "
   157	    "subsection shall affect regulatory determinations under section 6935 of this title. In "
   158	    "revising any regulation under section 6921 of this title identifying additional "
   159	    "characteristics of hazardous waste or listing any additional substance as hazardous waste "
   160	    "subject to this subchapter, the Administrator may require any person referred to in the "
   161	    "preceding provisions to file with the Administrator (or with States having authorized "
   162	    "hazardous waste permit programs under section 6926 of this title) the notification described "
   163	    "in the preceding provisions. Not more than one such notification shall be required to be "
   164	    "filed with respect to the same substance. No identified or listed hazardous waste subject to "
   165	    "this subchapter may be transported, treated, stored, or disposed of unless notification has "
   166	    "been given as required under this subsection. (b) Effective date of regulation The "
   167	    "regulations under this subchapter respecting requirements applicable to the generation, "
   168	    "transportation, treatment, storage, or disposal of hazardous waste (including requirements "
   169	    "respecting permits for such treatment, storage, or disposal) shall take effect on the date "
   170	    "six months after the date of promulgation thereof (or six months after the date of revision "
   171	    "in the case of any regulation which is revised after the date required for promulgation "
   172	    "thereof). At the time a regulation is promulgated, the Administrator may provide for a "
   173	    "shorter period prior to the effective date, or an immediate effective date for: (1) a "
   174	    "regulation with which the Administrator finds the regulated community does not need six "
   175	    "months to come into compliance; (2) a regulation which responds to an emergency situation; "
   176	    "or (3) other good cause found and published with the regulation. (Pub. L. 89–272, title II, "
   177	    "§3010, as added Pub. L. 94–580, §2, Oct. 21, 1976, 90 Stat. 2812; amended Pub. L. 96–482, "
   178	    "§15, Oct. 21, 1980, 94 Stat. 2342; Pub. L. 98–616, title II, §§204(a), 234, Nov. 8, 1984, 98 "
   179	    "Stat. 3235, 3258.) Editorial Notes Amendments 1984 —Subsec. (a). Pub. L. 98–616, §204(a), "
   180	    "inserted provisions after first sentence relating to burning and blending of hazardous "
   181	    "wastes and substituted \"the preceding provisions\" for \"the preceding sentence\" in three "
   182	    "places. Subsec. (b). Pub. L. 98–616, §234, inserted provision that at the time a regulation "
   183	    "is promulgated, the Administrator may provide for a shorter period prior to the effective "
   184	    "date, or an immediate effective date for a regulation with which the Administrator finds the "
   185	    "regulated community does not need six months to come into compliance, a regulation which "
   186	    "responds to an emergency situation, or other good cause found and published with the "
   187	    "regulation. 1980 —Subsec. (a). Pub. L. 96–482 struck out \"or revision\" after \"after "
   188	    "promulgation or revision of regulations\" and inserted provision for filing of notification "
   189	    "when revising any regulation identifying additional characteristics of hazardous waste or "
   190	    "listing any additional substance as hazardous waste subject to this subchapter. Executive "
   191	    "Documents Transfer of Functions For transfer of certain enforcement functions of "
   192	    "Administrator or other official of Environmental Protection Agency under this chapter to "
   193	    "Federal Inspector, Office of Federal Inspector for the Alaska Natural Gas Transportation "
   194	    "System, and subsequent transfer to Secretary of Energy, then to Federal Coordinator for "
   195	    "Alaska Natural Gas Transportation Projects, see note set out under section 6903 of this "
   196	    "title. 1 So in original. Probably should be followed by a semicolon."
